# CCGS-Lite Workflow Gates

- Start each feature with a short brief: player value, scope, and acceptance criteria.
- Before coding, list assumptions and technical risks that can trigger rework.
- Implement in small increments and validate after each increment.
- For non-trivial changes, include at least one test strategy (EditMode, PlayMode, or manual steps).
- When finishing, report changed files, what was tested, and remaining risks.
